# Foundation hardening (single entry point)

This project closed a **five-slice** foundation-hardening pass: lint, types, tests, docs, and validation. (The validation slice was tracked as an orthogonal axis through 2026-05-18 and promoted to a landed slice on 2026-05-19 per `docs/rfcs/0003-validation-library-adoption.md` — committed to Zod v4.) The synthesis layer is the canonical entry point; the per-slice docs are the sources of truth.

## Read first when relevant

Project-local synthesis + per-slice docs (paths relative to repo root):

- `docs/FOUNDATION-HARDENING.md` — synthesis layer, the four slices at a glance, the cross-slice findings, the plugin-pack handoff manifest.
- `docs/LINTING.md` — ESLint slice (HIGH-light → HIGH-staged → HIGH-full; the `npm run lint` strict gate).
- `docs/TYPING.md` — TypeScript slice (`tsc --noEmit` baseline + the 6 candidate strict flags + the per-workspace CI gate).
- `docs/TESTING.md` — testing slice (L1 unit through L5 Playwright layers + the layered test-mapping discipline).
- `docs/DOCS-README-STANDARDS.md` — docs slice (module-README template + audit checklist + the structural CI gate).
- `docs/CONTRACTS-VALIDATION-STRATEGY.md` v2.0 — validation slice (decision: Zod v4; library-agnostic `ValidatedSchema<T>` boundary in `@brewery/module-sdk` for third parties).
- `docs/rfcs/0003-validation-library-adoption.md` — RFC committing the validation slice to Zod v4 (Decisions A–G, spike evidence, migration plan).

If a referenced doc is absent in this project, proceed with the generic guidance in this rule's body and ask only for values that are necessary for the task.

## Why this exists

The foundation hardening pass invested in *bug-prevention foundations* (lint + types + tests) plus *contributor-experience foundation* (docs) over a multi-week period. CI gates enforce the floor, but every gate fails *after* the violation reaches the codebase. The plugin pack (this rule + its siblings under `45-tsjs-module-readme-standard.mdc` here, plus `22-`, `23-`, `23a-`, `26-`, `44-` in the companion `umbraculum-node-react-cursor-assistant` plugin) prevents violations at authoring time, before the gate fires. Both layers compound; neither substitutes for the other.

